com.i2group.apollo.networksearchservice.transport
Class NetworkSearchNode

java.lang.Object
  com.i2group.apollo.networksearchservice.transport.NetworkSearchNode
Direct Known Subclasses:
EntityNetworkSearchNode, LinkNetworkSearchNode
public abstract class NetworkSearchNode
extends Object

A generic representation for EntityNetworkSearchNodes and LinkNetworkSearchNodes that provides the features that are common to both.

A NetworkSearchNode contains a SearchNode that defines the criteria that an Item must match. The other contents of a NetworkSearchNode enable it to be identified and controlled in the context of a network search operation.

Since:
4.0

NetworkSearchNode

protected NetworkSearchNode(String nodeId,
                            SearchNode searchNode,
                            boolean isOutputEnabled,
                            List<String> disabledFilterInfoIds)
Constructs a new NetworkSearchNode, initializing all mandatory fields.

Parameters:
nodeId - A String containing an identifier for this NetworkSearchNode that must be unique within the network of nodes.
searchNode - The SearchNode that this NetworkSearchNode contains.
isOutputEnabled - true if Items that matched this NetworkSearchNode should be included in the network search results; false otherwise.
disabledFilterInfoIds - Strings identifying FilterInfos within the SearchNode that will not be applied when the network search involving this NetworkSearchNode takes place.

getCountCondition

public final ItemCountCondition getCountCondition()
Gets the ItemCountCondition for this NetworkSearchNode.

Within a NetworkSearchNodeList, there can be at most one EntityNetworkSearchNode with an ItemCountCondition. A LinkNetworkSearchNode cannot have an ItemCountCondition.

Returns:
See above, or null if there is no ItemCountCondition for this NetworkSearchNode.

setCountCondition

public final void setCountCondition(ItemCountCondition countCondition)
Sets the ItemCountCondition for this NetworkSearchNode.

Within a NetworkSearchNodeList, there can be at most one EntityNetworkSearchNode with an ItemCountCondition. A LinkNetworkSearchNode cannot have an ItemCountCondition.

Parameters:
countCondition - The ItemCountCondition to be set, or null to remove the ItemCountCondition from this NetworkSearchNode.
